-----------------------------------------------
Usage: pandahook build coreos HOOK-TYPE COMMAND
-----------------------------------------------
Follow any command with "help" for more information.

coreos automates the process of writing githook scripts with CoreOS.

HOOK-TYPE is a name that informs git when to activate the githook after it has been
placed into the hook-server. It is also the file-name of the generated script.
The generated file is placed into the working directory.  Note: The filename
must conform to one of the githook type names (post-receive, etc)

COMMAND specifies which common action the generator should script.

Available Commands
---------------------------
  restart   Restarts every listed service file



